list.item:
If Allies desire regeneration of Russia on democratic
                                    constitutional basis, they must definitely first condemn
                                    Bolshevik rule;

Allies should help Russia form a strong central government
                                    around which all sane elements would group themselves against
                                    Bolsheviks and Germans;

Such a government could be formed either in or out of
                                    Russia—like government of Venizelos—and later transferred to
                                    Russia;
